Petkim to Sell Air Separation Unit to Air Liquide Turkey Unit

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-09-28T04:39:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/petkim-to-sell-air-separation-unit-to-air-liquide-turkey-unit.html
Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM) ,
Turkey’s biggest chemicals maker, will sell its air separation
unit for $39 million to  Air Liquide SA (AI) ’s Turkish unit by Sept.
30 to improve productivity.  Petkim will also lease the land on which the air separation
unit stands to Air Liquide after final agreements are signed, it
said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange after the
market closed yesterday. Petkim and Air Liquide Gaz Sanayii &
Ticaret AS signed a goodwill agreement in December for
production and supply of industrial gases and building a new air
separation unit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Aydan Eksin at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net  